HEADWORD: Peristeropodous
<hw>Pe*ris`ter*op"o*dous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>peristera`</grk> a pigeon + <grk>poy`s</grk>, <grk>podo`s</grk>,
foot.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having pigeonlike feet; -- said of
those gallinaceous birds that rest on all four toes, as the curassows
and megapods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peristole</ent>⟦br⟧
